<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Cedarius</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I am a level 7 Wood elf ranger and have a few questions.  <BR>I just bought a banded waist armour for 6pp. Was that a good deal? I offer it to a merchant to check value and he offers me 1pp and a 4gp. How does one know the value of equipment?  Also, can I get training in any other city but my own? (kelethin) and what should I be training on.. I have spent a lot of trainings on "Sense Heading" but it still doesn't work.. I think my compass is broken.  I use /loc all the time anyways so perhaps I don't need to waste any more on sense heading.  Should I train in a new weapon such as 2HS? I look forward to your advice.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Morpeth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The going rate for banded tends to be about 1pp per AC point - so if you're banded waist armour has an AC value of 6 or greater you did fine. <P>You can get training in SureFall Glade as well. I have heard that the new patch was going to offer at least one more place to train - but I'm not sure where or who it was.<P>Sense heading is valuable in my opinion, it just takes a while to up it. My understanding is that it is success based - so failures don't count. Once you get some successes, you can start moving it up reasonably quickly - I find it's a very handy skill. Whenever I'm on a boat, resting/healing, waiting, etc. I click away, mine is about 70 now and I succeed about 2/3 of the time. Just be patient you'll get there.<P>I'm not a fan of 2H weapons, I think the speed to damage ratio isn't as good. Plus later on (17th I believe) you'll get dual wield - so personally I stay with 1H slash and 1H pierce. Most rangers I know don't use 2H much.<P>Hope this helps - enjoy!<P>Morpeth<BR>13th Season Ranger - E'ci<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Rini</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Oh no, don't dump any practices into senseheading!!! The trick is you make it a hotkey and just keep clicking it CONSTANTLY whevere you are, whatever you're doing. I even keep pressing it during battle, as it doesn't interfere at all. Just be patient and keep clicking it.  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Rane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">You can use /loc to determine heading too. Sense Heading is VERY slow to get going. I find it is worthwhile to dump like 5 practicve points into it just to give it a little shove, and then hotkey it as already mentioned. As times goes on, you'll find that this is the first skill to max out each time you level, and it is a very useful skill imo.<P>Ranger's had 2 guilds--Kelethin, and Surefall Glade (onear Qeynos). The recent patch added a Ranger GM named Morin Shadowbane in Kithicor forrest which adjoins the toen of Rivervale<P>Rane Westwind<BR>The Divine Alliance</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">fiannor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana"> Cedarius, I am a 7th lev wood elf ranger  also. I heard from some people that you should save up your points for spells later, or hobby skills, as many of the combat and wilderness skills go up with use. I know of one person who is 9th lev, and has only ever spent 1 point, (on magic to start getting manna I think).  I put mine in one hand slashing at first, and some in forage and sense heading, but I will save for a while now. In fact i was going to anyway cause I hated having to go back to Kelethin or to Surefall to train. <BR>    I was wondering too if there were only 2 places to train for a ranger. The third in kithicor would be wonderfull, especially since the Mysty thicket is nearby. Do you know if it is allready implimented Rane?<P>Fi</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Kuvander</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The guildmaster has been activated in Kithicor forrest. Her name is Morin Shadowbane. She can be found near the Commens zone off the path to the North.<P>------------------<BR>Ranger of the 41'st Tier<BR> Kuvander NightWind - MM<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
